The paper presents a generative model for people in clothing based on image data, which involves learning to generate a semantic segmentation of the body and clothing, and a conditional model on the resulting segments that creates realistic images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, as it involves learning from image data and generating new images. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category, as it deals with generating realistic images of people in clothing. The Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category may also be relevant, as the paper involves generating images of people in different clothing items and styles. Finally, the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category may also be relevant, as the paper involves a data-driven approach to people generation.
